  "prompt": "What license do I need for starting manufacturing of herbal diet products?",
  "response": "To start manufacturing herbal diet products, you'll typically need several licenses and permits:\n\n1. Business Licenses\n- General business license from your state/local government\n- Manufacturer's business license\n- Sales tax permit\n\n2. FDA Requirements\n- Register your facility with FDA\n- Follow Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP)\n- Comply with dietary supplement regulations\n\n3. Specific Herbal/Dietary Supplement Licenses\n- Dietary supplement manufacturing license\n- State-specific herbal product manufacturing permit\n\n4. Additional Considerations\n- Food processing license\n- Ingredient sourcing certifications\n- Product testing and quality control documentation\n\n5. Recommended Professional Certifications\n- HACCP (Hazard Analysis Critical Control Point)\n- ISO 22000 certification\n\n6. Legal Documentation\n- Product labeling compliance\n- Ingredient documentation\n- Health claim substantiation\n\nSpecific requirements can vary by:\n- State regulations\n- Product composition\n- Manufacturing location\n- Distribution method\n\nRecommended steps:\n- Consult local regulatory agencies\n- Contact FDA for specific guidelines\n- Hire a regulatory compliance consultant\n- Get professional legal advice\n\nEach jurisdiction might have unique requirements, so thorough research is crucial.",
